$ cmd.exe: colored output with echo

In → Windows/versions/10, it is possible to write → design/graphic/color[colored] output using the → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/commands/echo[`echo`] command. This is demonstrated with the following simple
→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/batch-files:
gh|about-cmd.exe|/commands/echo/colored-output.bat||

The script, when run on a black background, prints
gh|about-cmd.exe|/commands/echo/img/colored-output.png||


